description: Triangle of number of connected graphs with k >= 1 edges and n nodes (2 <= n <= k+1).
references: G. A. Baker et al., High-temperature expansions for the spin-1/2 Heisenberg model, Phys. Rev., 164 (1967), 800-817.
example: 1; 0 1; 0 1 2; 0 0 2 3; 0 0 1 5 6; ... (so with 5 edges there's 1 graph with 4 nodes, 5 with 5 nodes and 1 with 6 nodes).
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
